<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-16T01:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-16T01:29:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1227</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-16T01:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1917—1 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 14, 6 p.m. The President has answered <hi rend="italic">Montana</hi> asking object of formal armistice. He has no
                            information as to need for formal declaration, but states a practical
                            armistice already exists, as he is making no advance toward
                            Guantanamo.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>